Question: Madeline wants to plant 20 flowers in her garden. She assumes that about half of the seeds she plants will die before they bloom. However, the flower shop only sells packs of seeds with 25 seeds per pack. Each pack is $5. How much will Madeline spend on seeds to plant 20 flowers?
Answer: 10
Response: <reasoning>To figure out how much Madeline needs to spend, we first need to figure out how many seeds she will buy to get 20 flowers that are likely to bloom. Since half of her planned seeds will probably die, she will need 20 * 2 = 40 seeds. Since seeds come in packs, she needs to figure out how many packs she needs. Each pack has 25 seeds, so she needs to buy  40 / 25 = 1.6 packs. Since she cannot buy half a pack, Madeline will need to buy 2 packs, costing her 2 * $5 = $10. </reasoning>
 <answer>10</answer>
<end_of_turn>
